1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:22,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.xyz Support Admin)

2
00:00:50,049 --> 00:00:51,134
ALL FIGURES,
INCIDENTS, LOCATIONS,

3
00:00:51,217 --> 00:00:52,469
ORGANIZATIONS,
AND OTHERS ARE FICTITIOUS.

4
00:00:52,552 --> 00:00:53,970
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

5
00:00:54,054 --> 00:00:54,971
IN ACCORDANCE WITH GUIDELINES.

6
00:01:01,895 --> 00:01:06,316
SHIN I-RANG, HAN NA-HYUN
LAW OFFICE

7
00:01:16,117 --> 00:01:18,453
How may I help you?

8
00:01:20,038 --> 00:01:21,164
Ma'am!

9
00:01:26,127 --> 00:01:29,339
So that's why I didn't see you lately.

10
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:32,258
Did you pass away?

11
00:01:35,011 --> 00:01:37,806
You struggled so much,
only to pass away like this.

12
00:01:39,474 --> 00:01:41,226
-Ouch!
-What are you saying?

13
00:01:41,810 --> 00:01:44,145
I'm not dead yet.

14
00:01:44,229 --> 00:01:45,230
Oh.

15
00:01:46,856 --> 00:01:49,526
-Geez.
-You really aren't dead!

16
00:01:50,860 --> 00:01:52,153
Thank you.

17
00:01:52,237 --> 00:01:53,571
Thank you so much.

18
00:01:53,655 --> 00:01:56,658
You silly young man.

19
00:01:56,741 --> 00:01:57,742
Unbelievable.

20
00:01:57,826 --> 00:01:59,828
You came early.
I bought some coffee for you.

21
00:02:01,204 --> 00:02:02,664
Hello.

22
00:02:02,747 --> 00:02:03,915
Oh, dear.

23
00:02:06,084 --> 00:02:07,293
I can see her too.

24
00:02:07,377 --> 00:02:08,920
Attorney Han, this is…

25
00:02:14,175 --> 00:02:16,052
I can even touch her.

26
00:02:17,220 --> 00:02:19,681
Of course, you can. She's not a ghost.

27
00:02:21,182 --> 00:02:22,183
She's not?

28
00:02:22,267 --> 00:02:25,145
Why are you both so eager to call me dead?

29
00:02:25,228 --> 00:02:27,522
-I'm sorry.
-Sorry about that.

30
00:02:28,690 --> 00:02:30,859
Ma'am, why don't we sit down and talk?

31
00:02:30,942 --> 00:02:32,068
Sure.

32
00:02:39,868 --> 00:02:40,910
Who is she?

33
00:02:41,452 --> 00:02:43,913
She's a close acquaintance of mine.

34
00:02:46,291 --> 00:02:48,793
What brings you here?

35
00:02:48,877 --> 00:02:51,713
I'm here to meet you, young attorney.

36
00:02:51,796 --> 00:02:52,797
Why?

37
00:02:52,881 --> 00:02:54,799
Did you get caught up in any trouble?

38
00:02:56,801 --> 00:02:58,386
No, nothing like that.

39
00:02:59,262 --> 00:03:01,472
It's because of my late husband.

40
00:03:11,149 --> 00:03:15,612
Does he perhaps have
silver hair, bushy eyebrows…

41
00:03:18,031 --> 00:03:19,115
and a handsome face?

42
00:03:19,198 --> 00:03:20,325
Oh, my.

43
00:03:21,284 --> 00:03:24,078
Words say the attorney here is
nearly psychic.

44
00:03:24,162 --> 00:03:25,705
It must be true.

45
00:03:26,289 --> 00:03:28,333
An attorney doesn't need psychic powers.

46
00:03:28,416 --> 00:03:30,668
Oh, my head!

47
00:03:33,630 --> 00:03:37,383
Did your husband have
some kind of disease?

48
00:03:37,967 --> 00:03:38,968
Well,

49
00:03:39,802 --> 00:03:41,012
he had Alzheimer's.

50
00:03:43,139 --> 00:03:46,392
He came back to his senses
from time to time,

51
00:03:47,143 --> 00:03:50,438
but most of the time,
he only had memories of his earlier years.

52
00:03:50,521 --> 00:03:52,148
It must've been hard.

53
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:06,955
Did he perhaps have something
to do with shoes?

54
00:04:07,038 --> 00:04:09,540
How did you know?

55
00:04:09,624 --> 00:04:12,126
He was a shoemaker.

56
00:04:14,629 --> 00:04:16,965
Even when we met the first time,

57
00:04:18,174 --> 00:04:20,134
he was making shoes.

58
00:04:21,761 --> 00:04:23,137
YEAR 1979

59
00:04:24,973 --> 00:04:27,684
He was awfully rude to me.

60
00:04:27,767 --> 00:04:30,186
-At the time…
-So I…

61
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:33,815
…Seoul was a magical city
where everything changed overnight.

62
00:04:33,898 --> 00:04:37,568
I was a young girl with splendid dreams.

63
00:04:37,652 --> 00:04:39,696
Still, he's a premed student
at Hanguk University.

64
00:04:39,779 --> 00:04:41,864
Isn't he great husband material?

65
00:04:42,448 --> 00:04:44,325
So what if he's great husband material?

66
00:04:44,409 --> 00:04:46,119
I'm the one who's going to be the best.

67
00:04:47,287 --> 00:04:48,871
That sounds so like you.

68
00:04:50,581 --> 00:04:52,500
Even so, it's a shame.

69
00:04:52,583 --> 00:04:55,670
There isn't anyone suited to be
your husband as much as he is.

70
00:04:57,839 --> 00:04:59,299
What are you doing?

71
00:05:00,675 --> 00:05:02,135
I'm leaving without you.

72
00:05:03,344 --> 00:05:04,929
He's so cool.

73
00:05:23,197 --> 00:05:24,282
Are you here for new shoes?

74
00:05:24,907 --> 00:05:25,908
Excuse me?

75
00:05:26,492 --> 00:05:28,870
The showroom is over there.
This is the workshop.

76
00:05:28,953 --> 00:05:30,288
I know that.

77
00:05:30,955 --> 00:05:33,416
And what I need isn't new shoes…

78
00:05:37,462 --> 00:05:38,880
but you.

79
00:05:40,590 --> 00:05:44,844
Back then, I was preparing
to open my own shop

80
00:05:44,927 --> 00:05:47,472
with the marriage fund
I got from my parents

81
00:05:47,555 --> 00:05:50,308
after graduating
from a famous fashion academy.

82
00:05:50,391 --> 00:05:53,478
Shoes that make you happy
as soon as you wear them.

83
00:05:54,145 --> 00:05:57,065
Shoes that feel like
they will take you somewhere nice.

84
00:05:58,399 --> 00:06:01,694
To make the finest shoes
made with sincerity.

85
00:06:01,778 --> 00:06:03,112
That was my dream.

86
00:06:03,654 --> 00:06:05,615
MERRY SHOES

87
00:06:07,658 --> 00:06:11,204
The best kind of shoes aren't made
simply with money and skills.

88
00:06:11,871 --> 00:06:14,957
Without fine leather,
the best kind of shoes cannot exist.

89
00:06:15,041 --> 00:06:17,585
I also know
that quality leather is a must.

90
00:06:18,544 --> 00:06:20,213
Which company's leather do you want?

91
00:06:21,130 --> 00:06:22,256
Is it imported leather?

92
00:06:23,633 --> 00:06:25,718
From Italy? France?

93
00:06:30,765 --> 00:06:32,391
There's someone I want you to meet.

94
00:06:37,063 --> 00:06:38,898
Seon Hwa was from Hamgyong, North Korea.

95
00:06:38,981 --> 00:06:41,234
-Seon Hwa.
-She burnished the leather alone

96
00:06:41,317 --> 00:06:43,986
without anyone's help.

97
00:06:44,070 --> 00:06:47,907
Her leather was soft like a feather,
yet strong like metal.

98
00:06:47,990 --> 00:06:50,701
I fell in love with it straightaway.

99
00:06:50,785 --> 00:06:51,994
IDEAL SHOES

100
00:06:52,078 --> 00:06:53,412
Don't be nervous.

101
00:06:54,288 --> 00:06:55,748
Everyone, relax.

102
00:06:55,832 --> 00:06:57,834
One, two, three.

103
00:07:00,419 --> 00:07:02,547
-One more time.
-That was how

104
00:07:02,630 --> 00:07:05,341
-we opened Ideal Shoes.
-One, two, three.

105
00:07:06,259 --> 00:07:08,970
Ideal Shoes? Do you mean that Ideal Shoes?

106
00:07:09,053 --> 00:07:11,305
Yes, that's the one.

107
00:07:12,098 --> 00:07:13,182
Seriously?

108
00:07:13,266 --> 00:07:15,977
My heels right now are Ideal Shoes.

109
00:07:17,395 --> 00:07:18,646
Oh, that.

110
00:07:18,729 --> 00:07:22,733
It's from our steady-selling line
that's been produced since 1981.

111
00:07:24,110 --> 00:07:25,653
You have an eye for shoes.

112
00:07:26,904 --> 00:07:27,905
Wow.

113
00:07:28,573 --> 00:07:30,616
I see you in a whole new light.

114
00:07:32,243 --> 00:07:35,663
But why did you quit working?

115
00:07:35,746 --> 00:07:37,248
You're still healthy and well.

116
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:42,211
I had to focus on something
more important than work.

117
00:07:43,796 --> 00:07:45,173
Anyway,

118
00:07:45,882 --> 00:07:50,386
the three of us opened this shop alone
with a small budget,

119
00:07:50,470 --> 00:07:53,681
but we were confident
in the products we made.

120
00:08:40,770 --> 00:08:44,148
-They're so pretty.
-That's how our shoes

121
00:08:44,232 --> 00:08:46,609
started to fill the display cabinets.

122
00:08:47,944 --> 00:08:51,781
More and more people loved our products.

123
00:08:51,864 --> 00:08:53,199
One, two, three.

124
00:08:54,116 --> 00:08:57,537
-Smile a little more.
-We'd make shoes all night,

125
00:08:57,620 --> 00:08:59,789
but we couldn't stop smiling.

126
00:08:59,872 --> 00:09:00,873
IDEAL SHOES

127
00:09:00,957 --> 00:09:02,124
Get in closer.

128
00:09:02,208 --> 00:09:03,918
One, two, three.

129
00:09:08,839 --> 00:09:11,217
It was when I learned

130
00:09:11,300 --> 00:09:16,264
that Seon Hwa left behind
her newborn baby in North Korea.

131
00:09:16,806 --> 00:09:17,807
What are you doing?

132
00:09:19,183 --> 00:09:20,726
I was making a wish.

133
00:09:21,352 --> 00:09:25,022
To meet my son in North Korea again.

134
00:09:28,651 --> 00:09:29,652
Oh.

135
00:09:30,903 --> 00:09:32,280
I'll also make a prayer

136
00:09:32,863 --> 00:09:34,615
for your wish to come true.

137
00:09:36,117 --> 00:09:37,118
Me too.

138
00:09:39,787 --> 00:09:43,541
We felt like we had the world.

139
00:09:44,250 --> 00:09:45,751
We had nothing to fear.

140
00:09:55,219 --> 00:09:56,220
Not until

141
00:09:57,388 --> 00:09:59,181
Seon Hwa got arrested.

142
00:10:01,684 --> 00:10:03,477
She was accused of being a spy.

143
00:10:04,854 --> 00:10:05,855
It turned out

144
00:10:07,315 --> 00:10:09,483
Seon Hwa was sending money to North Korea.

145
00:10:12,278 --> 00:10:13,279
Let me go!

146
00:10:13,904 --> 00:10:17,658
She explained that the money was
for her family in the North.

147
00:10:17,742 --> 00:10:20,494
-Wait. Let go!
-She's innocent.

148
00:10:20,578 --> 00:10:22,788
-She isn't a spy.
-Seon Hwa!

149
00:10:22,872 --> 00:10:24,040
However,

150
00:10:25,041 --> 00:10:27,084
what we got in return
was a frightening threat.

151
00:10:28,628 --> 00:10:30,838
They questioned if we were also involved.

152
00:10:31,505 --> 00:10:34,467
If so, Ideal Shoes was
to close down right away.

153
00:10:36,385 --> 00:10:39,347
My husband and I couldn't say a thing.

154
00:10:40,848 --> 00:10:43,142
If the company closed down,

155
00:10:44,101 --> 00:10:47,605
dozens of employees were to go jobless.

156
00:10:48,272 --> 00:10:50,816
And their families added up to hundreds.

157
00:10:53,444 --> 00:10:54,445
In the end,

158
00:10:55,071 --> 00:10:59,367
we could do nothing
but hope that she'd be released safely.

159
00:11:01,285 --> 00:11:03,746
The years went by.

160
00:11:04,455 --> 00:11:06,624
When we went to visit her,

161
00:11:08,042 --> 00:11:09,418
she was

162
00:11:09,502 --> 00:11:11,545
already dead.

163
00:11:13,839 --> 00:11:18,219
We made her grave on a hill
where North Korea was visible

164
00:11:19,178 --> 00:11:21,639
and buried her cremation urn there.

165
00:11:22,890 --> 00:11:24,558
It was devastating.

166
00:11:26,644 --> 00:11:30,523
Only if we had visited her sooner…

167
00:11:31,232 --> 00:11:35,694
Only if we hadn't cared about the company
and saved her…

168
00:11:37,405 --> 00:11:40,741
Then, she may still be alive.

169
00:11:42,618 --> 00:11:46,997
Struggling with regret,
we made up our minds

170
00:11:48,499 --> 00:11:51,377
to find her son in North Korea

171
00:11:51,460 --> 00:11:52,962
and give her share to him.

172
00:11:53,045 --> 00:11:54,713
Please make sure to find him.

173
00:11:55,798 --> 00:11:56,799
I'm sorry.

174
00:11:57,550 --> 00:12:00,344
I see. Thank you
for your hard work, though.

175
00:12:00,428 --> 00:12:01,429
I'm sorry.

176
00:12:01,512 --> 00:12:03,764
I see. Thank you.

177
00:12:04,473 --> 00:12:05,558
We appreciate it.

178
00:12:06,225 --> 00:12:10,271
But it wasn't easy to find her son.

179
00:12:10,354 --> 00:12:11,439
WILL

180
00:12:11,522 --> 00:12:13,357
My husband ended up

181
00:12:14,233 --> 00:12:18,696
writing a will about leaving him
an inheritance out of anxiety.

182
00:12:20,156 --> 00:12:24,118
And after a year since he passed away,

183
00:12:24,827 --> 00:12:26,078
her son,

184
00:12:26,162 --> 00:12:29,707
Cha Eun Seong, was found at last.

185
00:12:30,916 --> 00:12:33,210
It says the heir must provide

186
00:12:33,294 --> 00:12:35,880
one-third of the inheritance
to Ms. Ryeo Seon Hwa's son,

187
00:12:35,963 --> 00:12:38,507
Cha Eun Seong, if he is found at any time.

188
00:12:38,591 --> 00:12:40,926
Most of the inheritance is
the shares of Ideal Shoes.

189
00:12:41,427 --> 00:12:44,680
The company will be at stake
if one-third of it is given to him.

190
00:12:45,931 --> 00:12:50,227
Ms. Ryeo Seon Hwa's contributions
to Ideal Shoes are mentioned as a reason.

191
00:12:51,604 --> 00:12:55,483
The case will be in our favor
if your mother is against this will.

192
00:12:55,566 --> 00:12:56,650
What's her opinion?

193
00:12:57,318 --> 00:13:00,404
My mother thinks it's only right
to do as my father's will says.

194
00:13:01,113 --> 00:13:04,742
She told Cha Eun Seong
about my father's will herself.

195
00:13:06,452 --> 00:13:07,870
She's always been like this.

196
00:13:07,953 --> 00:13:10,539
She can't stand to enjoy any luxuries

197
00:13:12,166 --> 00:13:14,084
when Ms. Ryeo wrongfully
passed away in prison.

198
00:13:14,168 --> 00:13:17,755
-Thank you. Have a great day.
-Thank you. Enjoy.

199
00:13:18,297 --> 00:13:20,382
She lives alone in an old, small house.

200
00:13:21,091 --> 00:13:24,094
She sells vegetables on the street
no matter how hard I try to stop her.

201
00:13:24,178 --> 00:13:25,304
Welcome.

202
00:13:26,347 --> 00:13:28,432
Normally, she lets me
have my way with everything.

203
00:13:28,933 --> 00:13:31,602
But she thundered at me
when I refused to give the money.

204
00:13:32,186 --> 00:13:35,564
She said she'd even take it to court
if she needed to.

205
00:13:37,650 --> 00:13:38,651
I see.

206
00:13:39,527 --> 00:13:41,070
All right for now.

207
00:13:41,153 --> 00:13:43,405
We'll have to check more in detail,

208
00:13:43,489 --> 00:13:45,282
but the deceased's will exists

209
00:13:45,366 --> 00:13:48,410
along with your mother's strong intention
to execute it.

210
00:13:48,494 --> 00:13:50,079
Thus, a trial seems inevitable.

211
00:13:50,162 --> 00:13:53,082
Then, we must win this case.

212
00:14:00,631 --> 00:14:03,342
Why don't you try persuading your son?

213
00:14:04,009 --> 00:14:07,972
You'll have to go to trial
against your son at this rate.

214
00:14:08,889 --> 00:14:10,516
It'll be tough.

215
00:14:10,599 --> 00:14:13,185
I've already tried.

216
00:14:13,769 --> 00:14:15,271
He's adamant.

217
00:14:15,854 --> 00:14:17,064
That's understandable.

218
00:14:17,731 --> 00:14:21,819
I honestly doubt your son could accept it.

219
00:14:22,319 --> 00:14:25,155
Not unless you compromised
with a much lower amount.

220
00:14:25,239 --> 00:14:27,199
I won't compromise.

221
00:14:27,283 --> 00:14:29,285
I'll never settle for a lower amount.

222
00:14:29,994 --> 00:14:32,413
Even if it's taken to court,

223
00:14:32,997 --> 00:14:35,040
I want to follow my husband's will.

224
00:14:35,749 --> 00:14:37,084
But…

225
00:14:37,167 --> 00:14:38,419
Okay.

226
00:14:38,502 --> 00:14:40,588
We understand, ma'am.

227
00:14:41,171 --> 00:14:43,257
Please go home for today.

228
00:14:43,340 --> 00:14:46,635
We'll get back to you
after a thorough check.

229
00:14:47,761 --> 00:14:48,762
Oh…

230
00:14:50,681 --> 00:14:51,765
Here.

231
00:14:53,267 --> 00:14:56,562
You can find materials and pictures
about Seon Hwa in this envelope.

232
00:14:56,645 --> 00:14:59,899
My number is in it too.

233
00:15:00,524 --> 00:15:04,570
Please help me keep my husband's promise.

234
00:15:07,615 --> 00:15:08,699
We'll see what can be done.

235
00:15:10,910 --> 00:15:11,994
Oh, right.

236
00:15:12,077 --> 00:15:14,330
We need to know about your husband

237
00:15:14,413 --> 00:15:16,874
if we're to prepare for the trial.

238
00:15:17,499 --> 00:15:20,127
May I know his name and date of birth?

239
00:15:20,210 --> 00:15:22,087
His name is

240
00:15:22,630 --> 00:15:24,006
Kang Dong-sik.

241
00:15:25,049 --> 00:15:29,845
He was born on March 1, 1953.

242
00:15:31,722 --> 00:15:33,223
I'll be counting on you.

243
00:15:44,985 --> 00:15:46,654
WILL

244
00:16:10,386 --> 00:16:11,929
Hello, sir.

245
00:16:12,012 --> 00:16:13,013
How do you do?

246
00:16:13,097 --> 00:16:17,142
I'm Kang Dong-sik, the shoemaker.

247
00:16:17,226 --> 00:16:19,061
I'm Attorney Shin I-rang.

248
00:16:19,144 --> 00:16:21,230
This is Attorney Han Na-hyun.

249
00:16:23,065 --> 00:16:25,442
Hello, I'm Attorney Han Na-hyun.

250
00:16:25,526 --> 00:16:27,820
I'm right here.

251
00:16:29,655 --> 00:16:32,533
-Oh, right. You can't see me.
-He's over there.

252
00:16:33,367 --> 00:16:34,952
It's nice to meet you.

253
00:16:35,035 --> 00:16:36,537
He says it's nice to meet you.

254
00:16:37,287 --> 00:16:39,790
Anyway, I see

255
00:16:39,873 --> 00:16:42,126
you're easygoing

256
00:16:42,209 --> 00:16:46,130
and practical, yet polished.

257
00:16:47,256 --> 00:16:50,509
And you mostly sit
with your left leg crossed.

258
00:16:51,385 --> 00:16:53,512
How did you know?

259
00:16:54,388 --> 00:16:57,349
One's shoes tell everything about them.

260
00:16:58,684 --> 00:17:02,896
You've worn those uncomfortable shoes
until the heels are frayed.

261
00:17:02,980 --> 00:17:05,315
It means you have
an easygoing personality.

262
00:17:05,983 --> 00:17:07,860
Those are machine-stitched shoes

263
00:17:07,943 --> 00:17:10,112
made with synthetic leather,

264
00:17:10,195 --> 00:17:13,323
but you chose a classic design.

265
00:17:13,991 --> 00:17:16,535
It means your taste isn't half bad.

266
00:17:16,618 --> 00:17:17,953
Gosh.

267
00:17:18,037 --> 00:17:22,791
The right heel is frayed
more than the left heel

268
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:25,794
because your pelvis is misaligned
from crossing your legs.

269
00:17:26,295 --> 00:17:29,715
But it's not too serious, so don't worry.

270
00:17:30,382 --> 00:17:32,676
Wow, amazing.

271
00:17:34,636 --> 00:17:36,013
What is it? What did he say?

272
00:17:37,097 --> 00:17:40,392
He got it all right about me
just by looking at my shoes.

273
00:17:42,561 --> 00:17:45,564
What about the old lady from earlier?

274
00:17:46,565 --> 00:17:48,067
I could sense

275
00:17:48,609 --> 00:17:52,946
a diligent and humble nature
from her shoes.

276
00:17:55,491 --> 00:17:58,118
He doesn't recognize Ms. Chae.

277
00:17:59,536 --> 00:18:02,414
Can you hand me one of the pictures
we got from her?

278
00:18:03,248 --> 00:18:05,250
What if he possesses you?

279
00:18:05,834 --> 00:18:08,337
We need to do anything
to help him regain his memory.

280
00:18:09,505 --> 00:18:13,300
And he doesn't seem dangerous.
It might be okay even if he possesses me.

281
00:18:24,895 --> 00:18:27,564
IDEAL SHOES

282
00:18:38,951 --> 00:18:39,952
Oh, boy.

283
00:18:40,702 --> 00:18:41,745
I'm running late.

284
00:18:44,123 --> 00:18:47,751
Where's the young man that was just here?

285
00:18:49,294 --> 00:18:51,964
Excuse me for asking, miss stranger,

286
00:18:52,589 --> 00:18:55,175
but where is the nearest bus stop?

287
00:18:55,759 --> 00:18:57,177
Why do you ask?

288
00:18:57,261 --> 00:18:59,847
I need to go to Malli-dong to make shoes.

289
00:19:00,639 --> 00:19:04,351
Customers will be disappointed
if I don't have the shoes ready on time.

290
00:19:04,434 --> 00:19:05,602
This is bad.

291
00:19:07,271 --> 00:19:08,397
Sir.

292
00:19:09,356 --> 00:19:11,525
Malli-dong isn't the same anymore.

293
00:19:12,109 --> 00:19:14,862
What? What do you mean by that?

294
00:19:17,030 --> 00:19:18,574
What I mean is--

295
00:19:18,657 --> 00:19:19,700
Miss.

296
00:19:19,783 --> 00:19:21,660
I'm really sorry,

297
00:19:21,743 --> 00:19:24,246
but I don't have time to hear you out.

298
00:19:25,747 --> 00:19:27,791
To my customers,

299
00:19:28,584 --> 00:19:30,252
my products mean more than just shoes.

300
00:19:30,878 --> 00:19:33,297
They're partners for success

301
00:19:33,380 --> 00:19:35,716
and life companions for their new lives.

302
00:19:38,218 --> 00:19:41,471
Oh, I'm running out of time.

303
00:19:41,555 --> 00:19:44,016
I have business there anyway.

304
00:19:44,099 --> 00:19:45,100
Let me accompany you.

305
00:19:45,184 --> 00:19:47,728
Sure, please lead the way.

306
00:19:53,108 --> 00:19:58,238
OKCHEON BUILDING

307
00:20:08,248 --> 00:20:10,500
Sir, please wait inside for a second.

308
00:20:10,584 --> 00:20:11,835
Okay.

309
00:20:47,704 --> 00:20:48,956
My goodness.

310
00:20:58,757 --> 00:21:00,300
-Excuse me, ma'am.
-Yes?

311
00:21:00,384 --> 00:21:03,053
-May I ask you something?
-Okay?

312
00:21:03,637 --> 00:21:07,307
What bus should I take
to get to Malli-dong?

313
00:21:07,391 --> 00:21:11,186
Bus number 0411
will take you straight there.

314
00:21:12,938 --> 00:21:14,273
Here it comes.

315
00:21:19,569 --> 00:21:20,988
Why, thank you.

316
00:21:21,071 --> 00:21:22,072
Sure.

317
00:21:28,161 --> 00:21:29,371
Wait!

318
00:21:47,681 --> 00:21:50,642
BUS 0411

319
00:21:52,936 --> 00:21:54,563
MALLI-DONG HANDMADE SHOE STREET

320
00:21:57,607 --> 00:22:00,152
Sir, please take me
to the handmade shoe street in Malli-dong.

321
00:22:00,235 --> 00:22:01,236
Okay.

322
00:22:13,623 --> 00:22:15,709
This must be the place.

323
00:22:18,128 --> 00:22:19,713
Welcome.

324
00:22:29,806 --> 00:22:32,225
How strange.

325
00:22:34,269 --> 00:22:36,146
This has to be the place.

326
00:22:36,813 --> 00:22:38,148
Excuse me.

327
00:22:38,815 --> 00:22:40,400
What are you looking for?

328
00:22:44,321 --> 00:22:45,822
Do you need anything?

329
00:22:45,906 --> 00:22:49,284
This is supposed to be my workshop.

330
00:22:49,367 --> 00:22:51,286
What's all this flashy stuff?

331
00:22:51,369 --> 00:22:52,662
Who are you, mister?

332
00:22:52,746 --> 00:22:55,373
I'm a shoemaker.

333
00:22:55,957 --> 00:22:57,959
-Where are my shoes?
-Get out.

334
00:22:58,043 --> 00:23:00,253
This place is my workshop.

335
00:23:00,337 --> 00:23:03,173
-There's no workshop here. Get out.
-What's the matter with you?

336
00:23:07,219 --> 00:23:08,887
This has to be it.

337
00:24:00,230 --> 00:24:01,648
Attorney Shin!

338
00:25:36,993 --> 00:25:39,246
Here, try it on.

339
00:25:46,211 --> 00:25:47,295
I'm sorry.

340
00:25:48,505 --> 00:25:50,715
I thought he'd remember something

341
00:25:51,216 --> 00:25:53,551
if I took him out
and let him see things for himself.

342
00:25:55,011 --> 00:25:56,638
I shouldn't have.

343
00:25:59,557 --> 00:26:00,558
Excuse me,

344
00:26:01,977 --> 00:26:03,895
but do you know me?

345
00:26:26,668 --> 00:26:29,129
You must've been so lonely alone.

346
00:26:33,800 --> 00:26:35,635
I'll help you from now on.

347
00:26:59,117 --> 00:27:02,704
SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE

348
00:27:07,667 --> 00:27:09,461
What are you going to do with this case?

349
00:27:09,544 --> 00:27:12,672
I think we should settle at a fair level.

350
00:27:13,673 --> 00:27:14,841
You think so?

351
00:27:17,010 --> 00:27:21,931
I believe my duty as her attorney is
to help her execute her husband's will.

352
00:27:24,559 --> 00:27:25,810
It's not likely, is it?

353
00:27:30,648 --> 00:27:32,484
Nevertheless, you'll fight to the end.

354
00:27:36,988 --> 00:27:38,198
I get it now.

355
00:27:38,990 --> 00:27:40,700
I'll have to work my butt off.

356
00:27:41,284 --> 00:27:43,036
Are you going to help me?

357
00:27:43,119 --> 00:27:46,164
We share this office,
and you're up against Taebaek.

358
00:27:46,956 --> 00:27:49,084
It would be heartless
to let you fight alone.

359
00:27:49,626 --> 00:27:52,212
Instead, we'll split
the contingency fee fifty-fifty.

360
00:27:57,258 --> 00:27:58,385
Deal.

361
00:28:12,982 --> 00:28:16,528
Father, did you give the Ideal Shoes case
to someone else?

362
00:28:16,611 --> 00:28:17,946
I did.

363
00:28:18,530 --> 00:28:21,324
Why? I even consulted
with CEO Kang Ji-hoon myself.

364
00:28:21,408 --> 00:28:23,910
Shin I-rang and Han Na-hyun
are defending the other side.

365
00:28:25,620 --> 00:28:26,621
So what?

366
00:28:30,166 --> 00:28:32,502
Personal feelings may hinder
an attorney's judgment.

367
00:28:32,585 --> 00:28:34,796
So, I had someone else take charge of it.

368
00:28:34,879 --> 00:28:37,966
No, I have no personal feelings.

369
00:28:39,384 --> 00:28:40,385
Let me do it.

370
00:28:41,094 --> 00:28:43,805
I'll prove myself, Father.

371
00:29:00,238 --> 00:29:01,489
You're saying

372
00:29:01,573 --> 00:29:03,783
this is where I used to live?

373
00:29:06,035 --> 00:29:08,037
I don't remember,

374
00:29:09,581 --> 00:29:11,833
but it feels very familiar.

375
00:29:14,836 --> 00:29:16,421
WORKROOM

376
00:29:43,656 --> 00:29:45,074
This is…

377
00:29:45,158 --> 00:29:46,618
What was it…

378
00:29:50,580 --> 00:29:52,999
What is it? Do you remember anything?

379
00:29:54,000 --> 00:29:56,836
What was this again?

380
00:29:58,838 --> 00:30:00,256
So, these…

381
00:30:05,887 --> 00:30:08,264
used to belong to my husband.

382
00:30:08,348 --> 00:30:10,350
I couldn't throw them out.

383
00:30:14,562 --> 00:30:16,397
It's a relief we have a lot to refer to.

384
00:30:16,481 --> 00:30:17,941
Thank goodness.

385
00:30:20,235 --> 00:30:22,237
Look at this old thing.

386
00:30:32,080 --> 00:30:34,958
Oh, my goodness.
I-rang, what are you doing?

387
00:30:35,041 --> 00:30:37,961
Don't wear this kind of thing!

388
00:30:38,545 --> 00:30:39,546
Sir.

389
00:30:39,629 --> 00:30:42,757
His shoes are for easy wear.

390
00:30:42,841 --> 00:30:45,051
So what if they're easy to wear?

391
00:30:45,134 --> 00:30:46,970
They're classless!

392
00:30:47,720 --> 00:30:48,847
Bah!

393
00:30:49,764 --> 00:30:51,933
-Hmph.
-I-rang!

394
00:30:52,016 --> 00:30:53,977
Seriously? This is the fifth floor!

395
00:30:54,060 --> 00:30:55,311
Geez!

396
00:30:57,063 --> 00:31:00,108
Let me start the briefing
about Kang Ji-hoon's will contest.

397
00:31:01,776 --> 00:31:03,987
"Will. I, Kang Dong-sik,
leave this as my last will."

398
00:31:04,070 --> 00:31:07,282
We must focus on this date.

399
00:31:07,365 --> 00:31:08,616
That needs to be checked.

400
00:31:08,700 --> 00:31:10,159
I'm putting Attorney Oh on it.

401
00:31:10,243 --> 00:31:11,870
Excuse me. Let me ask you something.

402
00:31:11,953 --> 00:31:13,162
-Yes?
-Well…

403
00:31:14,205 --> 00:31:16,040
Do you know these people?

404
00:31:16,124 --> 00:31:17,333
IDEAL SHOES

405
00:31:17,959 --> 00:31:19,252
No, I don't.

406
00:31:20,628 --> 00:31:22,922
I see. Thank you.

407
00:31:35,727 --> 00:31:36,811
Hello.

408
00:31:42,442 --> 00:31:44,903
Do you perhaps know these people?

409
00:32:05,298 --> 00:32:06,299
Let's go.

410
00:32:16,809 --> 00:32:18,061
2010 COMMERCIAL
2015 COMMERCIAL

411
00:32:21,773 --> 00:32:23,066
WHY OLD KOREANS LEAVE A WILL

412
00:32:23,858 --> 00:32:25,193
TESTIMONY
KANG JI-HOON, IDEAL SHOES CEO

413
00:32:25,276 --> 00:32:28,863
Now that we've visited the field
and collected enough materials,

414
00:32:29,739 --> 00:32:32,533
why don't we go meet Mr. Cha Eun Seong,
Ms. Ryeo Seon Hwa's son?

415
00:32:33,451 --> 00:32:34,494
Give it to me!

416
00:32:35,161 --> 00:32:36,913
I said no to these shoes!

417
00:32:37,413 --> 00:32:39,832
-Take the other one off immediately!
-Attorney Han, stop him!

418
00:32:39,916 --> 00:32:40,917
Bah!

419
00:32:44,671 --> 00:32:46,005
Thanks, Attorney Han!

420
00:32:54,389 --> 00:32:56,265
Wow.

421
00:32:56,349 --> 00:32:58,935
It's leather.

422
00:33:03,523 --> 00:33:06,192
-Excuse me. May I ask you something?
-Yes?

423
00:33:06,776 --> 00:33:08,820
I'm looking for Mr. Cha Eun Seong.

424
00:33:08,903 --> 00:33:10,905
Our chief? He's over there.

425
00:33:11,614 --> 00:33:12,740
Chief.

426
00:33:21,708 --> 00:33:23,793
You're having a late lunch today.

427
00:33:23,876 --> 00:33:25,503
It's not good to skip meals.

428
00:33:25,586 --> 00:33:27,755
Come by anytime.

429
00:33:27,839 --> 00:33:29,007
Okay?

430
00:33:29,590 --> 00:33:31,426
And eat up.

431
00:33:31,509 --> 00:33:33,094
I will, ma'am.

432
00:33:33,678 --> 00:33:35,388
-Enjoy.
-Thank you.

433
00:33:37,432 --> 00:33:38,891
I eat here every day.

434
00:33:39,600 --> 00:33:40,810
Are you okay with noodles?

435
00:33:40,893 --> 00:33:43,104
I can handle anything.

436
00:33:48,484 --> 00:33:49,819
This is delicious.

437
00:33:49,902 --> 00:33:50,903
It's good.

438
00:33:58,453 --> 00:33:59,787
I'm all right.

439
00:34:00,413 --> 00:34:01,831
Feel free to ask me questions.

440
00:34:02,457 --> 00:34:05,543
When did you come to Korea?

441
00:34:06,169 --> 00:34:07,754
I hear your hometown is in North Korea.

442
00:34:08,421 --> 00:34:09,422
That's right.

443
00:34:10,298 --> 00:34:13,843
I was born in Hamgyong and separated
from my mother when I was one.

444
00:34:13,926 --> 00:34:17,013
After my aunt died,
I came to Korea more than ten years ago.

445
00:34:17,597 --> 00:34:21,059
How did you come
to dye leather for a living?

446
00:34:22,143 --> 00:34:24,145
My hometown is known for leather-dyeing.

447
00:34:24,228 --> 00:34:26,189
All my family and relatives
were in the field.

448
00:34:28,900 --> 00:34:31,778
When I heard my mother was
in the same line of work,

449
00:34:33,154 --> 00:34:34,572
it broke my heart.

450
00:34:35,948 --> 00:34:39,619
How much do you know about your mother?

451
00:34:40,203 --> 00:34:43,706
I heard she kept sending money
to my family in the North

452
00:34:43,790 --> 00:34:46,417
and tried to get us out of the country.

453
00:34:46,501 --> 00:34:50,004
And that she lost contact with us
as soon as we arrived in China.

454
00:34:54,133 --> 00:34:55,676
Moving on to the next story.

455
00:34:56,260 --> 00:34:59,388
"Today is the first death anniversary

456
00:34:59,472 --> 00:35:01,599
of my beloved wife."

457
00:35:02,391 --> 00:35:05,728
"I've been trying
to keep a level head for my children,

458
00:35:05,812 --> 00:35:07,855
but it's not so easy."

459
00:35:08,815 --> 00:35:11,818
"Whenever I listen to the songs she liked,

460
00:35:11,901 --> 00:35:14,320
pass by the road we often walked together,

461
00:35:15,154 --> 00:35:17,448
or look at the food we enjoyed together,

462
00:35:18,032 --> 00:35:19,450
I'm reminded of my wife."

463
00:35:20,201 --> 00:35:22,078
"I miss her so much"--

464
00:35:24,038 --> 00:35:26,707
He doesn't even know
that his mother passed away.

465
00:35:27,291 --> 00:35:28,584
I feel so bad for him.

466
00:35:30,336 --> 00:35:32,505
I guess Ms. Chae
couldn't possibly inform him

467
00:35:33,089 --> 00:35:35,007
of his mother's death.

468
00:35:35,591 --> 00:35:38,594
We'd better tell him eventually
when we get a chance.

469
00:35:51,190 --> 00:35:54,193
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

470
00:35:55,570 --> 00:35:57,947
Go in without me.
I'll park the truck and follow you.

471
00:35:58,030 --> 00:35:59,115
Wait.

472
00:36:04,162 --> 00:36:05,413
What is this?

473
00:36:13,337 --> 00:36:14,839
SHIN I-RANG

474
00:36:15,965 --> 00:36:18,384
Isn't this your phone number?

475
00:36:19,218 --> 00:36:20,678
In case you go missing again.

476
00:36:22,972 --> 00:36:25,850
-Attorney Han.
-To make it easier to look for you.

477
00:36:27,393 --> 00:36:28,811
Park and come up.

478
00:36:31,397 --> 00:36:35,943
OKCHEON BUILDING

479
00:36:43,701 --> 00:36:45,536
Oh, it must be love.

480
00:36:47,997 --> 00:36:50,208
It's nothing like that.

481
00:36:50,291 --> 00:36:52,668
Ghosts can see everything.

482
00:37:11,979 --> 00:37:13,231
That's right.

483
00:37:15,942 --> 00:37:18,653
This is love

484
00:37:55,564 --> 00:37:57,858
What should I do?

485
00:37:58,359 --> 00:38:01,946
If you suddenly leave me behind

486
00:38:36,981 --> 00:38:39,233
WORKROOM

487
00:39:36,040 --> 00:39:38,000
Even so, it's a shame.

488
00:39:38,084 --> 00:39:41,003
There isn't anyone suited to be
your husband as much as he is.

489
00:39:45,508 --> 00:39:46,967
He's so cool.

490
00:39:50,638 --> 00:39:52,848
DEAR DONG-SIK
…I CAN'T HIDE MY FEELINGS ANYMORE…

491
00:40:07,571 --> 00:40:11,325
DAEUN CHOCOLATE

492
00:41:17,975 --> 00:41:19,560
CONGRATS ON
HAN NA-HYUN'S GRAND OPENING

493
00:41:21,312 --> 00:41:22,730
What am I doing here?

494
00:41:25,733 --> 00:41:27,151
Snap out of it.

495
00:41:32,156 --> 00:41:34,158
SEOUL
VACANT

496
00:41:35,784 --> 00:41:38,746
Hi, Na-hyun. Are you still at the office?

497
00:41:39,246 --> 00:41:43,250
Your mom sent me to deliver a lunch box
for you and Attorney Shin.

498
00:41:43,792 --> 00:41:46,253
But I don't see any space to park.

499
00:41:46,795 --> 00:41:48,422
Okay, take your time coming downstairs.

500
00:41:48,506 --> 00:41:49,798
See you soon.

501
00:41:49,882 --> 00:41:51,258
Oops.

502
00:41:55,804 --> 00:41:56,805
Oh, my.

503
00:42:05,272 --> 00:42:06,398
What was that?

504
00:42:06,482 --> 00:42:07,608
Oh, no. I-I'm sorry.

505
00:42:07,691 --> 00:42:09,193
Were you even looking at the road?

506
00:42:09,276 --> 00:42:11,320
I'm so sorry, sir.

507
00:42:11,403 --> 00:42:12,571
Unbelievable.

508
00:42:13,572 --> 00:42:16,283
Repairing the bumper alone
would cost as much as your cab.

509
00:42:16,909 --> 00:42:17,910
I'm so sorry.

510
00:42:19,203 --> 00:42:20,204
Are you drunk?

511
00:42:20,788 --> 00:42:22,206
No, not at all.

512
00:42:22,289 --> 00:42:23,290
Dad?

513
00:42:23,832 --> 00:42:25,084
Oh, hey.

514
00:42:28,337 --> 00:42:29,380
My goodness.

515
00:42:29,964 --> 00:42:31,423
That's crumpled up bad.

516
00:42:31,507 --> 00:42:33,926
On second look, it's a minor scratch.

517
00:42:34,009 --> 00:42:35,344
-What?
-It's a scratch.

518
00:42:35,427 --> 00:42:36,762
No, I just crashed--

519
00:42:36,845 --> 00:42:38,305
It was already like this.

520
00:42:38,389 --> 00:42:40,808
It's all right. Are you not injured?

521
00:42:40,891 --> 00:42:42,810
I'm okay, but you--

522
00:42:42,893 --> 00:42:45,271
I'm okay because I'm young and strong.

523
00:42:45,354 --> 00:42:47,273
-Dad.
-Na-hyun.

524
00:42:48,274 --> 00:42:49,858
-Mr. Yang?
-Oh, hi.

525
00:42:50,442 --> 00:42:52,194
Do you know this man?

526
00:42:53,696 --> 00:42:57,199
You must be Attorney Han's father.

527
00:42:58,576 --> 00:43:02,371
Hello, I'm Managing Partner Yang Do-kyung
of her former workplace.

528
00:43:03,038 --> 00:43:05,958
Good lord, this is horrible.

529
00:43:06,750 --> 00:43:08,419
-Dear me.
-What's going on?

530
00:43:08,502 --> 00:43:11,714
Well, I was trying to stop
the lunch box from falling and…

531
00:43:11,797 --> 00:43:12,798
Oh.

532
00:43:13,507 --> 00:43:16,218
Sorry. We'll handle it through insurance.

533
00:43:16,302 --> 00:43:18,637
-Are you hurt?
-No, no. I'm not hurt.

534
00:43:18,721 --> 00:43:20,723
-I rammed into his car.
-Excuse me?

535
00:43:21,390 --> 00:43:23,601
No, I rammed into his car.

536
00:43:23,684 --> 00:43:26,061
What are you talking about?
I specialize in car accidents.

537
00:43:26,145 --> 00:43:28,105
I caused this accident, end of discussion.

538
00:43:28,689 --> 00:43:31,567
No, Na-hyun.
I really did ram into his car.

539
00:43:32,776 --> 00:43:34,361
What a complicated situation.

540
00:43:34,445 --> 00:43:36,363
I'll get going. I'll see you another time.

541
00:43:36,447 --> 00:43:37,448
Oh, okay.

542
00:43:37,990 --> 00:43:39,199
Mr. Yang.

543
00:43:39,283 --> 00:43:40,284
Yeah?

544
00:43:43,537 --> 00:43:45,748
-What is that?
-It's nothing.

545
00:43:45,831 --> 00:43:48,917
-Is it for me?
-No, it's for someone else.

546
00:43:49,543 --> 00:43:52,838
It says, "Congrats on
Han Na-hyun's grand opening."

547
00:43:56,884 --> 00:43:57,885
Oh, boy.

548
00:43:58,677 --> 00:43:59,887
Why is it written there?

549
00:44:01,263 --> 00:44:02,264
It's not for you.

550
00:44:17,905 --> 00:44:18,906
What the?

551
00:44:26,872 --> 00:44:29,208
What was I doing here?

552
00:44:31,210 --> 00:44:33,337
What did I do to make my hand like this?

553
00:44:36,882 --> 00:44:38,676
Where did my phone go?

554
00:44:40,803 --> 00:44:43,931
Sir, did something happen in your house?

555
00:44:44,515 --> 00:44:46,684
Yeah. I made shoes.

556
00:44:47,267 --> 00:44:48,644
-Shoes?
-Yes.

557
00:44:49,478 --> 00:44:50,479
Shoes for who?

558
00:44:53,524 --> 00:44:55,859
I can't remember.

559
00:45:10,416 --> 00:45:11,750
Why are you taking your shoes off?

560
00:45:12,960 --> 00:45:15,337
Oh, nothing. You're late.

561
00:45:16,088 --> 00:45:17,965
-Something came up.
-I see.

562
00:45:19,758 --> 00:45:21,385
Where did you get that plant?

563
00:45:22,428 --> 00:45:23,554
Guess what.

564
00:45:23,637 --> 00:45:26,348
Managing Partner Yang of Taebaek was here.

565
00:45:26,432 --> 00:45:28,183
-You mean, Yang Do-kyung?
-Yes.

566
00:45:29,518 --> 00:45:30,519
Where's Attorney Han?

567
00:45:30,602 --> 00:45:32,688
She stepped outside to see Mr. Yang off.

568
00:45:32,771 --> 00:45:34,523
Maybe they're having dinner together.

569
00:45:36,650 --> 00:45:38,068
Try calling her if you're curious.

570
00:45:38,152 --> 00:45:41,572
No, I don't think that's necessary.

571
00:45:45,951 --> 00:45:50,789
OKCHEON BUILDING

572
00:46:02,092 --> 00:46:03,093
SHIN I-RANG

573
00:46:04,470 --> 00:46:06,805
Takes a lot of work, doesn't it?

574
00:46:07,973 --> 00:46:10,309
I'm sorry. What did you just say?

575
00:46:11,018 --> 00:46:14,521
You've got to connect
two different individuals,

576
00:46:15,355 --> 00:46:17,024
smooth them out,

577
00:46:17,941 --> 00:46:21,195
and polish them from time to time,

578
00:46:21,278 --> 00:46:23,572
which is why it's so difficult.

579
00:46:24,865 --> 00:46:26,575
Both shoes

580
00:46:26,658 --> 00:46:28,118
and love.

581
00:46:30,329 --> 00:46:32,080
Love? What are you talking about?

582
00:46:32,164 --> 00:46:34,708
A ghost knows everything, brat.

583
00:46:37,002 --> 00:46:39,922
The two are also the same in a sense

584
00:46:40,005 --> 00:46:43,634
that they shine more
the more heart and soul you put into them.

585
00:46:45,135 --> 00:46:46,512
Oh, please.

586
00:46:53,727 --> 00:46:54,978
It's your brother-in-law.

587
00:46:55,521 --> 00:46:56,522
What?

588
00:46:58,065 --> 00:47:00,609
-I-rang.
-Bong-su?

589
00:47:07,866 --> 00:47:09,117
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

590
00:47:09,201 --> 00:47:11,787
Attorney Han, what brings you here
at this hour--

591
00:47:11,870 --> 00:47:13,789
Where were you?
You said you'd park and come up.

592
00:47:14,498 --> 00:47:17,626
-Oh, I--
-Why didn't you answer your phone?

593
00:47:17,709 --> 00:47:19,253
I lost my phone--

594
00:47:19,336 --> 00:47:22,548
Also, why did you leave work
by yourself without waiting for me?

595
00:47:22,631 --> 00:47:24,174
You made me worry.

596
00:47:25,676 --> 00:47:28,887
I heard you left with Mr. Yang.

597
00:47:28,971 --> 00:47:30,973
-I didn't want to disturb.
-Disturb?

598
00:47:31,765 --> 00:47:35,227
There was a car accident. I handled it
through insurance and left him hours ago.

599
00:47:35,727 --> 00:47:37,521
I had no idea that you were home.

600
00:47:37,604 --> 00:47:39,856
I took this and looked everywhere
in Malli-dong for you!

601
00:47:41,942 --> 00:47:42,943
Really?

602
00:47:44,069 --> 00:47:46,530
Are you angry?

603
00:47:49,449 --> 00:47:50,993
I'm not angry…

604
00:47:51,868 --> 00:47:54,204
I'm just tired. My feet hurt too.

605
00:48:03,213 --> 00:48:04,214
Thanks.

606
00:48:06,383 --> 00:48:08,093
Thanks for what? I said I'm tired.

607
00:48:08,677 --> 00:48:10,762
How can you be this bad
at reading emotions?

608
00:48:13,932 --> 00:48:16,685
I'm sorry. I'll never do it again.

609
00:48:16,768 --> 00:48:18,103
Why are you laughing?

610
00:48:19,938 --> 00:48:20,939
I'm sorry.

611
00:48:21,023 --> 00:48:22,691
You say sorry at everything.

612
00:48:24,151 --> 00:48:25,777
What's wrong with you, really?

613
00:48:28,113 --> 00:48:30,741
Beats me. Why do I keep apologizing?

614
00:48:37,831 --> 00:48:39,333
Did you have dinner?

615
00:48:40,292 --> 00:48:41,376
You think I did?

616
00:48:41,918 --> 00:48:44,921
Me neither. Care to have dinner with me?

617
00:48:46,798 --> 00:48:47,966
What are we having?

618
00:48:48,550 --> 00:48:50,552
I know a delicious place nearby.

619
00:49:06,151 --> 00:49:08,737
-Welcome!
-Welcome!

620
00:49:16,161 --> 00:49:17,454
You must be hungry.

621
00:49:17,537 --> 00:49:19,539
Eat all you want, Attorney Han.

622
00:49:20,123 --> 00:49:21,333
This is unusual of you.

623
00:49:21,917 --> 00:49:22,918
Is today a special day?

624
00:49:23,001 --> 00:49:24,586
No,

625
00:49:24,670 --> 00:49:27,589
but you had a tough day because of me.

626
00:49:28,548 --> 00:49:29,716
You'll regret it.

627
00:49:30,300 --> 00:49:31,551
I'm a sushi killer.

628
00:49:34,012 --> 00:49:35,013
Me too.

629
00:49:38,767 --> 00:49:40,477
Where's the tuna?

630
00:49:41,103 --> 00:49:42,854
We can make an order.

631
00:49:42,938 --> 00:49:44,606
-Excuse me.
-Yes?

632
00:49:44,690 --> 00:49:46,692
Could you make us
two plates of tuna sushi?

633
00:49:46,775 --> 00:49:48,193
-Coming right away.
-Thank you.

634
00:49:49,403 --> 00:49:51,822
Wow, it looks good.

635
00:49:53,907 --> 00:49:56,326
-Here's your tuna.
-Thank you.

636
00:49:57,369 --> 00:49:58,370
Here you go.

637
00:50:08,046 --> 00:50:09,548
This is really good.

638
00:50:25,105 --> 00:50:26,189
I see you're loving it.

639
00:50:30,485 --> 00:50:31,570
It's delicious.

640
00:50:37,075 --> 00:50:38,618
Where did my shoes go?

641
00:50:38,702 --> 00:50:41,830
Mom, my Heartsping shoes are missing too.

642
00:50:41,913 --> 00:50:45,000
-That's odd.
-I was going to wear them.

643
00:50:45,709 --> 00:50:47,085
Sir.

644
00:50:47,169 --> 00:50:50,922
Take a slow look at these as you wait.

645
00:50:52,257 --> 00:50:54,468
You brought your whole family's shoes.

646
00:50:55,177 --> 00:50:56,178
Oh, dear.

647
00:50:57,637 --> 00:50:59,181
-See you later.
-Okay.

648
00:51:00,223 --> 00:51:01,600
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

649
00:51:03,268 --> 00:51:04,603
Goodness, gracious.

650
00:51:05,896 --> 00:51:07,647
How are your feet?

651
00:51:09,024 --> 00:51:11,193
Let's please focus on the trial.

652
00:51:18,074 --> 00:51:19,701
Long time no see, sir.

653
00:51:20,368 --> 00:51:22,287
I'm so glad to see you well.

654
00:51:22,370 --> 00:51:25,081
It's been such a long time.

655
00:51:25,165 --> 00:51:27,209
I was sad that you left Taebaek.

656
00:51:27,876 --> 00:51:30,670
But I'm relieved
to see you work with Attorney Shin.

657
00:51:31,671 --> 00:51:33,757
All right. Let's play fair.

658
00:51:33,840 --> 00:51:34,841
Yes, sir.

659
00:51:43,934 --> 00:51:46,436
Aren't you being too sweet to Shin I-rang?

660
00:51:47,145 --> 00:51:48,146
Am I?

661
00:51:49,356 --> 00:51:50,649
Then again,

662
00:51:50,732 --> 00:51:53,985
you don't know what kind of freak he is.

663
00:52:17,384 --> 00:52:18,385
Oh, my.

664
00:52:22,055 --> 00:52:24,266
Why is this out here?

665
00:52:41,199 --> 00:52:42,200
This can't be.

666
00:52:45,203 --> 00:52:47,914
TO MY DEAR BELOVED H,
FROM DONG-SIK

667
00:52:55,380 --> 00:52:56,715
Hold on.

668
00:53:01,803 --> 00:53:07,976
Let the trial begin
for Case 2025-Gahab-1901458.

669
00:53:11,646 --> 00:53:13,315
Ms. Chae is running late.

670
00:53:15,317 --> 00:53:16,693
I know.

671
00:53:17,277 --> 00:53:18,278
Where's Mr. Kang?

672
00:53:18,945 --> 00:53:19,988
He's in the truck.

673
00:53:20,071 --> 00:53:21,907
He's not going to come. Don't worry.

674
00:53:24,200 --> 00:53:26,786
This trial has been convened
following the lawsuit

675
00:53:26,870 --> 00:53:30,874
filed by Plaintiff Kang Ji-hoon,
claiming that the will of his late father,

676
00:53:30,957 --> 00:53:33,877
Kang Dong-sik, is invalid
while Defendant Chae Jeong-hui,

677
00:53:33,960 --> 00:53:37,547
his mother, maintains
the mandatory execution of the will.

678
00:53:38,214 --> 00:53:41,343
Defense counsel,
you may begin your opening statement.

679
00:53:47,557 --> 00:53:51,478
In 1979, Kang Dong-sik, Chae Jeong-hui,
and Ryeo Seon Hwa opened Ideal Shoes

680
00:53:51,561 --> 00:53:56,316
in the alley for handmade shoes
in Malli-dong and became co-owners.

681
00:53:57,067 --> 00:54:01,237
I've submitted corporate documents
and pictures to prove this.

682
00:54:01,321 --> 00:54:02,739
EXHIBITS 2-1, 2-2, 4-1, 4-3

683
00:54:04,324 --> 00:54:07,661
Ms. Ryeo Seon Hwa's leatherworking skills

684
00:54:07,744 --> 00:54:11,498
served as a foundation
for the growth of their business.

685
00:54:11,581 --> 00:54:15,752
In recognition of her contributions,
the late Chairman Kang Dong-sik

686
00:54:15,835 --> 00:54:20,799
left a will to bequeath one-third
of the inheritance to Ms. Ryeo's son.

687
00:54:34,521 --> 00:54:37,691
Therefore, as the representative
of the defendant,

688
00:54:37,774 --> 00:54:40,443
I demand that Plaintiff Kang Ji-hoon

689
00:54:40,527 --> 00:54:44,572
promptly execute the will
of the late Chairman Kang Dong-sik

690
00:54:44,656 --> 00:54:48,076
and transfer one-third of the inheritance
to Ms. Ryeo's son, Cha Eun Seong.

691
00:54:48,159 --> 00:54:49,244
That is all.

692
00:55:04,134 --> 00:55:07,470
We'd love to carry out the will…

693
00:55:09,639 --> 00:55:12,559
if the chairman's will is genuine.

694
00:55:13,685 --> 00:55:17,063
Ms. Chae Jeong-hui, the wife
of the late Chairman Kang Dong-sik,

695
00:55:17,147 --> 00:55:20,025
has proved it to be
her husband's handwriting.

696
00:55:22,235 --> 00:55:23,236
That's right.

697
00:55:24,612 --> 00:55:26,948
With the help of the Korea Institute
of Document Examination,

698
00:55:27,032 --> 00:55:28,533
a thorough analysis of the will

699
00:55:29,117 --> 00:55:32,912
shows that the will was indeed
written by the chairman.

700
00:55:32,996 --> 00:55:35,498
But the problem lies elsewhere.

701
00:55:36,958 --> 00:55:37,959
Attorney Shin I-rang.

702
00:55:39,002 --> 00:55:41,546
Will you tell me
when the will was written?

703
00:55:44,257 --> 00:55:46,885
What for?
It obviously says so on the will.

704
00:55:46,968 --> 00:55:49,345
Please tell me when it was written.

705
00:55:54,684 --> 00:55:57,854
June 12, 2019.

706
00:55:58,772 --> 00:56:02,150
Correct, and that is the problem.

707
00:56:02,233 --> 00:56:03,485
Why is that a problem?

708
00:56:04,319 --> 00:56:08,031
Chairman Kang Dong-sik's symptoms
of Alzheimer's worsened in 2021.

709
00:56:08,615 --> 00:56:12,744
And the will was written in 2019,
which is 2 years before that.

710
00:56:12,827 --> 00:56:16,331
Was it really written in 2019?

711
00:56:21,628 --> 00:56:23,129
WILL
I, KANG DONG-SIK…

712
00:56:24,422 --> 00:56:26,883
WILL

713
00:56:27,467 --> 00:56:31,304
The analysis result
of the ink used in the will shows

714
00:56:31,387 --> 00:56:34,974
that it was written
with a Napoleon fountain pen.

715
00:56:35,058 --> 00:56:36,810
The company of this fountain pen

716
00:56:36,893 --> 00:56:39,979
raised the pH level of its black ink

717
00:56:40,063 --> 00:56:44,776
from 6.7 to 7.2 to improve its smoothness
in November of 2022.

718
00:56:45,527 --> 00:56:46,736
Surprisingly enough,

719
00:56:47,320 --> 00:56:51,533
the pH level of the ink used in the will,
which was supposedly written in June 2019,

720
00:56:51,616 --> 00:56:53,326
turned out to be 7.2.

721
00:56:55,036 --> 00:56:59,040
Thus, it cannot be established as fact
that the will was written in June 2019.

722
00:56:59,874 --> 00:57:02,210
Besides, in November of 2022,

723
00:57:02,293 --> 00:57:05,171
the chairman could not recognize his wife

724
00:57:05,255 --> 00:57:07,549
as well as his own son
due to severe dementia.

725
00:57:08,591 --> 00:57:11,761
Attached is a expert testimony
from a medical specialist.

726
00:57:11,845 --> 00:57:12,971
Objection!

727
00:57:13,054 --> 00:57:14,055
Let us hear more.

728
00:57:15,098 --> 00:57:16,099
Thank you.

729
00:57:16,850 --> 00:57:17,976
Now,

730
00:57:18,059 --> 00:57:22,605
if the will wasn't written by the chairman
whose disease was worsening at the time,

731
00:57:23,440 --> 00:57:26,484
who could it be that wrote the will?

732
00:57:32,740 --> 00:57:35,285
Through document anti-forgery software,

733
00:57:35,368 --> 00:57:38,037
we examined the similarities
between the will

734
00:57:38,121 --> 00:57:40,123
and the writings
of another particular person.

735
00:57:40,206 --> 00:57:41,207
The result shows

736
00:57:41,791 --> 00:57:45,044
that the usage frequency
of conjunctive words and pronouns

737
00:57:45,128 --> 00:57:48,089
and the placement of verbs
match by more than 94%.

738
00:57:49,841 --> 00:57:51,342
This particular person is…

739
00:58:05,648 --> 00:58:07,275
DAEUN CHOCOLATE

740
00:58:22,707 --> 00:58:23,750
Are you done?

741
00:58:23,833 --> 00:58:25,460
Yes, I'm almost done.

742
00:58:28,254 --> 00:58:30,006
They're beautiful.

743
00:58:30,924 --> 00:58:31,925
Aren't they?

744
00:59:17,554 --> 00:59:19,973
If you were sound of mind,

745
00:59:21,182 --> 00:59:24,060
you would've agreed with me.

746
00:59:26,020 --> 00:59:27,021
Honey.

747
00:59:29,190 --> 00:59:31,359
Please tell me you do.

748
00:59:41,327 --> 00:59:43,913
Now, hold this.

749
00:59:45,290 --> 00:59:46,374
Write.

750
00:59:47,292 --> 00:59:48,626
-Write?
-Yes.

751
00:59:52,046 --> 00:59:53,047
Write what?

752
00:59:53,756 --> 00:59:55,008
"Will."

753
00:59:58,595 --> 01:00:00,972
"I, Kang Dong-sik…"

754
01:00:01,055 --> 01:00:02,640
I, Kang Dong-sik…

755
01:00:02,724 --> 01:00:03,850
"…leave this…"

756
01:00:03,933 --> 01:00:07,186
…leave this as my last will.

757
01:00:08,730 --> 01:00:10,189
What…

758
01:00:10,273 --> 01:00:11,399
Honey.

759
01:00:11,482 --> 01:00:13,067
This particular person is…

760
01:00:14,444 --> 01:00:15,737
Ms. Chae Jeong-hui.

761
01:00:22,702 --> 01:00:23,870
His claim doesn't make sense.

762
01:00:23,953 --> 01:00:26,164
She has no reason to fabricate the will.

763
01:00:26,247 --> 01:00:27,999
Yes, she does.

764
01:00:29,000 --> 01:00:31,711
The one who reported Ms. Ryeo Seon Hwa
for being a spy…

765
01:00:32,712 --> 01:00:34,380
-Let go!
-She's not a spy.

766
01:00:34,464 --> 01:00:36,549
Seon Hwa!

767
01:00:36,633 --> 01:00:39,469
…was Ms. Chae Jeong-hui.

768
01:00:41,638 --> 01:00:43,097
It can't be.

769
01:00:46,643 --> 01:00:48,061
This is ridiculous!

770
01:00:49,354 --> 01:00:50,355
Honey.

771
01:00:51,814 --> 01:00:54,359
I submit the document
of the Military Intelligence Agency.

772
01:00:55,193 --> 01:00:56,527
INFORMANT: CHAE JEONG-HUI

773
01:00:58,154 --> 01:01:00,990
Honey! Why would you?

774
01:01:01,949 --> 01:01:07,455
The document clearly states that
Ms. Chae reported Ms. Ryeo Seon Hwa.

775
01:01:07,538 --> 01:01:09,874
We were not informed
of this evidence in advance.

776
01:01:09,957 --> 01:01:11,834
Ms. Chae reported Ms. Ryeo,

777
01:01:11,918 --> 01:01:14,003
but when Ms. Ryeo passed away in jail,

778
01:01:14,087 --> 01:01:17,715
she attempted to leave an inheritance
to her son, Cha Eun Seong,

779
01:01:17,799 --> 01:01:19,550
so that she could offset her guilt

780
01:01:20,760 --> 01:01:22,929
even by fabricating her husband's will.

781
01:01:27,308 --> 01:01:28,393
Honey!

782
01:01:35,525 --> 01:01:37,777
Now that the will is proven to be fake,

783
01:01:37,860 --> 01:01:40,196
the plaintiff has no duties
to share the inheritance

784
01:01:40,279 --> 01:01:41,572
with Ryeo Seon Hwa's son.

785
01:01:41,656 --> 01:01:42,824
No, Mr. Kang.

786
01:01:42,907 --> 01:01:45,201
-Not now, please.
-There's no reason to continue the trial.

787
01:01:45,785 --> 01:01:47,036
-What…
-Thus, I request…

788
01:01:47,120 --> 01:01:49,330
-Say what must be said!
-…a prompt conclusion

789
01:01:49,414 --> 01:01:50,665
of this trial.

790
01:01:52,875 --> 01:01:54,669
I wrote it!

791
01:01:59,590 --> 01:02:00,591
What?

792
01:02:00,675 --> 01:02:03,553
I wrote the will!

793
01:02:03,636 --> 01:02:04,637
Me!

794
01:02:04,721 --> 01:02:06,723
Defense counsel, what are you doing?

795
01:02:07,348 --> 01:02:10,184
Do you want to be ejected
for perjury and contempt of court?

796
01:02:10,268 --> 01:02:13,771
Hey, Mr. Judge.
Listen to what I have to say!

797
01:02:13,855 --> 01:02:14,897
I--

798
01:02:14,981 --> 01:02:16,149
Your Honor!

799
01:02:16,232 --> 01:02:18,484
Attorney Shin I-rang has
a serious chronic disease.

800
01:02:19,360 --> 01:02:23,114
I request a recess
due to his current condition.

801
01:02:23,197 --> 01:02:24,991
A recess, not a conclusion!

802
01:03:00,276 --> 01:03:03,196
TO MY DEAR BELOVED H,
FROM DONG-SIK

803
01:03:12,288 --> 01:03:14,207
Why did you report Ms. Ryeo?

804
01:03:14,290 --> 01:03:15,541
-I'm sorry.
-Honey.

805
01:03:15,625 --> 01:03:17,752
But he likes someone else.

806
01:03:17,835 --> 01:03:20,379
I saw you with him at the workshop.

807
01:03:20,463 --> 01:03:22,173
Seon Hwa!

808
01:03:22,256 --> 01:03:23,257
Let's give up on this case.

809
01:03:23,341 --> 01:03:26,594
What happens if Seon Hwa is alive?

810
01:03:26,677 --> 01:03:28,054
It'll be a complete game-changer.

811
01:03:28,137 --> 01:03:30,056
Find where Ryeo Seon Hwa
is buried immediately.

812
01:03:30,139 --> 01:03:31,641
Some people are looking for you.

813
01:03:31,724 --> 01:03:33,684
-Run away.
-It's Seon Hwa.

814
01:03:33,768 --> 01:03:35,353
It's her.

815
01:03:35,436 --> 01:03:39,774
Subtitle translation by: Eunjin Erica Kim
